name: $resourceType
desc: Returns the FHIR type name for this instance

name: $identifier
desc: Returns: Unique instance identifiers assigned to a device by manufacturers other organizations or owners.

name: $udiCarrier
desc: Returns: Unique device identifier (UDI) assigned to device label or package.  Note that the Device may include multiple udiCarriers as it either may include just the udiCarrier for the jurisdiction it is sold, or for multiple jurisdictions it could have been sold.

name: $addudiCarrier
desc: Unique device identifier (UDI) assigned to device label or package.  Note that the Device may include multiple udiCarriers as it either may include just the udiCarrier for the jurisdiction it is sold, or for multiple jurisdictions it could have been sold.

lvardefs.name: objRef
lvardefs.desc: Unique device identifier (UDI) assigned to device label or package.  Note that the Device may include multiple udiCarriers as it either may include just the udiCarrier for the jurisdiction it is sold, or for multiple jurisdictions it could have been sold.

name: $status
desc: Returns: Status of the Device availability.

desc: Reason for the dtatus of the Device availability.

lvardefs.name: objRef

name: $distinctIdentifier

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The serial number assigned by the organization when the device was manufactured.

name: $deviceName
desc: Returns: This represents the manufacturer's name of the device as provided by the device, from a UDI label, or by a person describing the Device.  This typically would be used when a person provides the name(s) or when the device represents one of the names available from DeviceDefinition.

name: $adddeviceName
desc: This represents the manufacturer's name of the device as provided by the device, from a UDI label, or by a person describing the Device.  This typically would be used when a person provides the name(s) or when the device represents one of the names available from DeviceDefinition.
